abstract.gco:CharacterString: U.S. Census Populated Place Areas represents populated place areas within the United States that include both incorporated places and census designated places identified by the U.S. Census Bureau.It is updated annually as Populated Place boundaries change. The geography is sourced from US Census Bureau 2020 TIGER FGDB (National Sub-State) and edited using TIGER Hydrology to add a detailed coastline for cartographic purposes. Geography last updated May 2022.Attribute fields include 2020 total population from the US Census PL94 data. The Population Class field values represent population ranges as follows:Population from 0 - 249Population from 250 - 499Population from 500 - 999Population from 1,000 - 2,499Population from 2,500 - 9,999Population from 10,000 - 49,999Population from 50,000 - 99,999Population from 100,000 - 249,999Population from 250,000 - 499,999Population 500,000 and overThis ready-to-use layer can be used within ArcGIS Pro, ArcGIS Online, its configurable apps, dashboards, Story Maps, custom apps, and mobile apps. Data can also be exported for offline workflows. Please cite the 'U.S. Census Bureau' when using this data.

purpose.gco:CharacterString: U.S. Census Populated Place Areas provides the boundaries and 2020 U.S. Census class, codes, and population information for the Census populated places of the United States.

credit.gco:CharacterString: Esri; U.S. Department of Commerce, Census Bureau; U.S. Department of Commerce (DOC), National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA), National Ocean Service (NOS), National Geodetic Survey (NGS)

measureDescription.gco:CharacterString: The dataset is converted to file geodatabase (FGDB) format using tools in ArcGIS. The geometry is checked, and if needed repaired.
After processing, the dataset is checked for drawing display and number of records and file sizes compared with source materials.

The positional accuracy of TIGER/Line varies with the source materials used. The Census Bureau cannot specify the accuracy of features changed or added by its field staff or through local updates, features derived from the GBF/DIME Files, or other sources. Thus, the level of positional accuracy in the TIGER/Line shapefiles makes them unsuitable for high-precision measurement applications such as engineering problems, property transfers, or other uses that might require highly accurate measurements of the earth's surface.

description.gco:CharacterString: The following steps were performed by Esri: Extracted the datasets from Census TIGER/Line Shapefiles and merged them into a nationwide file geodatabase. Projected the dataset to WGS 1984. Clipped the dataset to the coastline with Data and Maps 2019 U.S. States. Added the fields CLASS, ST, STFIPS, and PLACEFIPS with values from the Census TIGER/Line Shapefiles fields. Removed and renamed fields. Added the field POPULATION (alias POP2018). Added the field POP_CLASS (based on POPULATION) and recalculated it with the same range breaks. Added the field SQMI and calculated its values projected to North America Albers Equal Area Conic. Added and calculated the field POP_SQMI (alias POP18_SQMI).
